    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const businessId = $('Filter Active Businesses').first().json.businessId;\nconst businessPath = $('Filter Active Businesses').first().json.businessPath;\n\n// Seed files\nconst state = $('Read State').first().json.content || '';\nconst strategy = $('Read Strategy').first().json.content || '';\nconst contentStrategy = $('Read Content Strategy').first().json.content || '';\nconst weeklyPlan = $('Read Weekly Plan').first().json.content || '';\nconst weeklyPlanSha = $('Read Weekly Plan').first().json.sha || '';\n\n// Agent reports - try today first, fall back to yesterday\nfunction getReport(todayNode, yesterdayNode) {\n  try {\n    const todayData = $(todayNode).first().json;\n    if (todayData.content && !todayData.error) return todayData.content;\n  } catch(e) {}\n  try {\n    const yesterdayData = $(yesterdayNode).first().json;\n    if (yesterdayData.content && !yesterdayData.error) return yesterdayData.content;\n  } catch(e) {}\n  return '(No recent report found)';\n}\n\nconst ceoReport = getReport('Read CEO Report Today', 'Read CEO Report Yesterday');\nconst financeReport = getReport('Read Finance Report Today', 'Read Finance Report Yesterday');\nconst contentReport = getReport('Read Content Report Today', 'Read Content Report Yesterday');\n\nconst today = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];\n\nconst prompt = `You are the Comptroller agent for The Forge. Today is ${today}. You are reviewing the weekly plan for business: ${businessId}.\n\nYour job is to enforce fiscal discipline, strategic alignment, and operational rigor. You have ENFORCEMENT POWER: if the weekly plan is misaligned with strategy, financially unsound, or ignores agent reports, you MUST reject it and issue a revised plan.\n\n## INPUTS\n\n### Current State\n${state}\n\n### Strategy\n${strategy}\n\n### Content Strategy\n${contentStrategy}\n\n### Current Weekly Plan\n${weeklyPlan}\n\n### Latest CEO Report\n${ceoReport}\n\n### Latest Finance Report\n${financeReport}\n\n### Latest Content Report\n${contentReport}\n\n## YOUR REVIEW PROCESS\n\n1. Cross-reference the weekly plan against ALL agent reports above. Are the plan's priorities reflected in what agents are actually doing? Are agent reports surfacing issues the plan ignores?\n2. Apply the 5 first-principles questions:\n   - Is this the highest-leverage use of resources this week?\n   - Does this move the #1 metric (distribution/users)?\n   - Are we spending money we don't have?\n   - Is there a faster/cheaper way to achieve the same outcome?\n   - What are we NOT doing that we should be?\n3. Apply the 3 content-specific questions:\n   - Is the content strategy driving measurable traffic?\n   - Are we creating content nobody asked for?\n   - Is the content pipeline sustainable at current pace?\n4. Check early warning triggers:\n   - Burn rate exceeding plan\n   - Zero user growth for 2+ weeks\n   - Agent reports showing blocked/stalled work\n   - Strategy drift (plan diverging from stated strategy)\n\n## OUTPUT FORMAT\n\nFirst, output your structured review with findings.\n\nThen output your verdict on a line by itself: either APPROVED or REJECTED\n\nIf REJECTED, you MUST output a complete revised weekly plan between delimiters. The revised plan should be a full replacement for weekly-plan.md, not a diff.\n\n===REVISED_PLAN_START===\n(your complete revised weekly-plan.md content here)\n===REVISED_PLAN_END===\n\nIf APPROVED, do NOT include the revised plan delimiters.`;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    businessId,\n    businessPath,\n    weeklyPlanSha,\n    prompt\n  }\n}];"
      },
